# LSP Servers - Language Server Protocol Support

## Built-in Servers

OpenCode includes built-in LSP server support for many languages:

| LSP Server | Language |
|------------|----------|
| astro | Astro |
| bash | Bash |
| clangd | C, C++ |
| csharp | C# |
| dart | Dart |
| deno | Deno |
| eslint | JavaScript, TypeScript |
| gopls | Go |
| kotlin-ls | Kotlin |
| lua-ls | Lua |
| pyright | Python |
| rust | Rust |
| svelte | Svelte |
| terraform | Terraform |
| typescript | TypeScript |
| vue | Vue |
| zls | Zig |
| And many more... | |

## How It Works

OpenCode automatically starts LSP servers for detected languages. LSP provides:
- Code completion
- Go to definition
- Find references
- Diagnostics and errors
- Hover information

## Configure

LSP servers are configured in the `lsp` section of `opencode.json`:

### Environment Variables
```json
{
  "lsp": {
    "env": {
      "NODE_OPTIONS": "--max-old-space-size=4096"
    }
  }
}
```

### Initialization Options
```json
{
  "lsp": {
    "initialization": {
      "typescript": {
        "provideFormatter": true
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### Disable All
```json
{
  "lsp": {
    "disable": true
  }
}
```

### Disable Specific
```json
{
  "lsp": {
    "disabled": ["eslint", "pyright"]
  }
}
```

### Command Override
```json
{
  "lsp": {
    "command": {
      "typescript": "/path/to/custom/typescript-language-server"
    }
  }
}
```

### Extensions
Map file extensions to specific LSP servers.

## Custom LSP Servers

Add custom LSP servers for languages not included in the built-in list:
```json
{
  "lsp": {
    "servers": {
      "my-language": {
        "command": "my-lsp-server",
        "extensions": [".mylang"]
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## PHP Intelephense License

For PHP development, PHP Intelephense requires a license key for full functionality. Configure it in the LSP settings.
